 碩士班課程 
課程名稱微電腦介面電路設計
課號IME6543
狀態開課中
開課年度101
學期2
上課時間Tue. EFG
選別elective (選修)
學分數3
上課地點EE229
授課教師鄭時龍 / 
先修科目或先備能力Microprocessor
課程概述與目標The interface is a hardware and/or software data transmission regulator that controls data exchange between the PC and other devices. The most common types of interfaces used in the modern PC are: Parallel, Serial, USB, EIDE / EDI / ATA / ATAPI, SCSI, and PC Card. This course will be focused on asynchronous serial communication standards, hardware, terminology, and concepts. Asynchronous serial communication products are used in industrial and commercial systems to transmit data bit-by-bit, or sequentially. The most important protocols or standards used for early serial communications are RS-232, RS-422 and RS-485. USB creates a method of accessing peripheral devices and solves several technical issues associated with old style peripherals. The course includes an overview of the primary concepts of USB transfers and describes the intersection between USB system software, system hardware and USB devices for USB 1.x systems and USB 2.0 system.
教科書1.	Universal Serial Bus System Architecture”, 2nd Edition, (Don Anderson/Dave Dzarko) 
2.	“Programming the Microsoft Windows Driver Model” (Oney) 
3.	“The 8051 Microcontroller Architecture, Programming, & Applications”, 2nd Edition, (Kenneth J. Ayala) 
4.	USB Implementers Forum web site: www. usb.org 
課程大綱單元主題	 
1.	RS232 Links 
2.	Windows Programming 
3.	Microcontroller Serial Ports 
4.	RS-485 Networks 
5.	USB Interfacing 
6.	USB Signaling Environment 
7.	USB Transfer Types & Packets 
8.	Error Recovery 
9.	Configuration Process
基本素質與核心能力&nbsp
學期作業及評量方式&nbsp
教學方法&nbsp
師生晤談&nbsp
每週進度表&nbsp
備註請同學遵守智慧財產權觀念及勿使用不法影印教科書。
